1
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:19,067
Amanda wants to put
her past behind her.

2
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,333
She's now happy
with her life.

3
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:24,000
Blessing, my foot.

4
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,200
She can't fool me!

5
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:28,667
She can't one-up me.

6
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,967
I still have an ace against her.

7
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:34,400
Are you breaking
up with me again?

8
00:00:34,567 --> 00:00:35,867
It's always like this.

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,733
You want to break up even
because of the small things.

10
00:00:39,867 --> 00:00:41,000
We've been through a lot.

11
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:43,133
We've overcome a
lot of problems.

12
00:00:43,267 --> 00:00:46,467
And in a snap, you
want to let go of me?

13
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,233
What is there to fight for?

14
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:49,233
Our baby's gone.

15
00:00:49,367 --> 00:00:52,267
And we're always fighting, Red.

16
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:54,667
You know the Ramoses, right?

17
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,033
Her son, Red.

18
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:58,667
It seems that Red
is most wanted tonight.

19
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:01,400
His girlfriend asked me
where he was earlier.

20
00:01:01,533 --> 00:01:03,233
His girlfriend is here?

21
00:01:03,367 --> 00:01:05,500
I don't want you to
break up with my son.

22
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:07,100
Eden, I'm sorry.

23
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:10,467
I'm sorry if that's what you got
from everything I said.

24
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:14,067
I know that I have been harsh
to you and Red lately.

25
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,933
Maybe because I've been stressed
from the threats

26
00:01:16,067 --> 00:01:18,000
I've been receiving.

27
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:19,767
You got your
enemies frightened.

28
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:22,100
Eden was here earlier.

29
00:01:22,233 --> 00:01:23,300
It seems that she and Red
are having trouble

30
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:24,933
with their relationship.

31
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:27,867
But Amanda, it isn't time yet.

32
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,500
We have plans.

33
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:31,000
You can't be distracted.

34
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:32,567
I still love you so much.

35
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:34,567
I love you so much too.

36
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:37,600
I'm glad the two of you
have patched things up.

37
00:01:37,733 --> 00:01:41,300
Thank you for letting me stay
even though our baby's gone.

38
00:01:41,467 --> 00:01:43,700
We're going to let
your baby rest, Eden.

39
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:46,800
And when we bury her, you
should also bury your love left

40
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:48,100
for your mother.

41
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:50,333
Did you know what she's
going through right now?

42
00:01:50,467 --> 00:01:53,667
Her baby died after
she gave birth.

43
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:54,600
What?
She said they got
into an accident

44
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:56,633
on their way to the hospital.

45
00:01:56,767 --> 00:02:00,633
And she was brought
to a midwife.

46
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:03,533
Only one person can hurt
my daughter like this.

47
00:02:03,667 --> 00:02:06,900
Probably she also had something
to do with the baby's death.

48
00:02:13,733 --> 00:02:16,000
Sweetie...

49
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:21,767
we didn't meet,
but I'm bidding you goodbye.

50
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:25,967
I'm sorry.

51
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:34,700
I'm sorry I couldn't protect you
from the person who hurt you...

52
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:36,700
from your own grandmother.

53
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:46,900
I will never forget you.

54
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:52,700
And will never forget
the person who did this to you.

55
00:02:54,867 --> 00:02:57,000
Because she killed you.

56
00:03:15,867 --> 00:03:17,833
Our baby's gone, Red.

57
00:03:22,833 --> 00:03:25,333
She was killed.

58
00:03:25,467 --> 00:03:27,367
My mom killed her.

59
00:03:47,433 --> 00:03:49,367
Don't worry, Yen.

60
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:53,333
Once we're both healed,
we can start a family again.

61
00:03:53,467 --> 00:03:56,300
Thank you, Red,
for understanding

62
00:03:56,467 --> 00:03:58,233
and for being patient with me.

63
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:04,633
I'm sure Baby
Chloe is now happy.

64
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,167
Because we're
still together.

65
00:04:09,033 --> 00:04:11,100
We still love each other.

66
00:04:13,367 --> 00:04:14,300
We love you, Yen.

67
00:04:16,533 --> 00:04:18,933
Right, Mom, Dad?

68
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:20,000
Of course, Sweetheart.

69
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:25,533
Eden...

70
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:32,300
from now on, call me mom.

71
00:04:32,467 --> 00:04:33,367
Okay?

72
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:39,333
Thank you, Mom.

73
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:48,500
Wait, before we leave...

74
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:50,300
I saw a restroom upstairs.

75
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:51,967
I'll go use it first.

76
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,467
I'll be right back, okay?

77
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,467
Okay.

78
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,833
Rina.

79
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:31,900
Amanda.

80
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:35,833
Did you also bury
someone here?

81
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,500
I can have you buried here.

82
00:05:38,633 --> 00:05:42,100
It depends on your
answer to my question.

83
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,367
Why are you grumpy again?

84
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:48,000
I thought you had moved on.

85
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:52,300
Didn't you say, "I'm so
blessed to be stressed?"

86
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:53,167
Right?

87
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:55,600
What did you do
to Yenyen's child?

88
00:06:03,267 --> 00:06:05,267
I knew it.

89
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:08,167
You had something to do
with her daughter's death.

90
00:06:11,533 --> 00:06:12,700
I can't do that.

91
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:15,300
I can't hurt my grandchild.

92
00:06:16,767 --> 00:06:20,367
Aren't you the child killer?

93
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,767
Not me.

94
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:28,367
You are so evil you
can do anything.

95
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:32,333
You're just putting on an act.

96
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:35,700
You want to exact revenge!

97
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:39,167
Anywhere and whoever
suffers, you don't care.

98
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:42,600
What did you do
to Yenyen's baby?

99
00:06:43,967 --> 00:06:48,533
Why are you accusing me?

100
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:51,967
Didn't you curse them?

101
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:54,467
This is your fault.

102
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,167
That's not true.

103
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:57,600
What's wrong with you?

104
00:06:58,700 --> 00:06:59,533
Amanda!

105
00:06:59,667 --> 00:07:01,400
No! Amanda!

106
00:07:02,267 --> 00:07:03,267
I knew it!

107
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,867
You still haven't changed!

108
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,500
You still behave
like a prisoner!

109
00:07:06,633 --> 00:07:08,567
And you, you thought you're
better than me?

110
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:13,333
And you, you're wealthy,
but you have no manners!

111
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:14,967
Stop it!

112
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:16,100
Amanda!

113
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,700
Get off me, Amanda!

114
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,067
You deserve that!

115
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:35,700
What's taking your mom so long?

116
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:36,733
You know her.

117
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:39,900
I'll go check on her.

118
00:07:41,433 --> 00:07:43,267
Something might have
happened to auntie...

119
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:44,533
I mean mom.

120
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:52,500
What time is it?

121
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:55,233
Gosh, long time.

122
00:07:58,333 --> 00:07:59,967
Your mom's bladder
is something.

123
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:01,767
I'm hungry.

124
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,600
You all deserve that!

125
00:08:05,333 --> 00:08:06,533
Get off her!

126
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:08,900
Are you okay, Mom?

127
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,600
Mom?

128
00:08:11,733 --> 00:08:14,767
I won't let you
hurt my mom!

129
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:15,800
Mom?

130
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:19,467
Did you call her mom?

131
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:22,967
And why not?

132
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:29,933
I was with her
throughout her pregnancy.

133
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:35,267
And when the baby died,
I took care of her.

134
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:40,600
While you are busy
moving on with your life.

135
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:44,133
And didn't you say
that you're off to live

136
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:46,167
without your daughter?

137
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:49,133
So you won't
have any problem.

138
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,067
Did you say that, Mom?

139
00:08:56,567 --> 00:08:59,267
You're brainwashing her.

140
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,333
How dare you.

141
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:03,300
Go on, Mom.

142
00:09:03,433 --> 00:09:06,567
If you don't want to
care for me, it's okay.

143
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:08,467
Just forget about me.

144
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:13,233
Just leave the people who
care for me out of it.

145
00:09:13,367 --> 00:09:14,800
Okay?

146
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,500
Sorry, Eden.

147
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:21,100
When will you move on, Mom?

148
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:25,667
I've lost a lot already.

149
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:28,400
You even got my baby involved.

150
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:32,000
I lost my baby, Mom!

151
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:33,700
I wasn't able to hold her.

152
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:35,967
To kiss her!

153
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:39,067
I wasn't even able to touch her!

154
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,167
Sorry.

155
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:42,100
Sorry?

156
00:09:42,233 --> 00:09:45,733
Can your apology
bring back my child?

157
00:09:45,867 --> 00:09:46,667
Mom, please.

158
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,900
Leave me alone!

159
00:09:49,033 --> 00:09:51,733
Let go of your hatred.

160
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:06,967
I can't believe
Amanda came back.

161
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:09,200
And she hurt you again.

162
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:11,500
I should have confronted her.

163
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:12,867
There's no need for that.

164
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:15,800
Eden defended me.

165
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:21,500
I know it is hard for you,

166
00:10:21,633 --> 00:10:24,900
but I'm glad you two have
already faced each other.

167
00:10:25,033 --> 00:10:28,700
At least you were able to tell
everything you wanted.

168
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:33,300
Just consider this as a closure.

169
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:35,800
But why did she attack you?

170
00:10:35,967 --> 00:10:38,367
I thought she didn't
hate you anymore?

171
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,467
She's just pretending!

172
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,400
During the party?

173
00:10:41,533 --> 00:10:43,600
She was faking!

174
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:44,400
Party?

175
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:46,833
Was my mom there
the other night?

176
00:10:48,967 --> 00:10:52,167
She was not just at the party.

177
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:53,800
She gave the party.

178
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:58,800
Lucho Madrigal is her husband.

179
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:02,933
She is Mrs. Madrigal.

180
00:11:04,933 --> 00:11:06,433
Husband?

181
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:09,333
I'm sorry.

182
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:15,833
We don't want you to get
hurt, but your mom has moved on

183
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:19,233
since she married
that wealthy man.

184
00:11:19,367 --> 00:11:20,900
She has forgotten about you.

185
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:27,267
She only remembered you
when she was threatening you.

186
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:31,633
Or when she wanted to hurt you
and our baby.

187
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:33,067
Leave her be, Red.

188
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:39,867
If she has forgotten about me,
maybe it's time for me

189
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,067
to forget my mom too.

190
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:02,333
So, the woman you wanted
to meet and impress so bad,

191
00:12:02,467 --> 00:12:07,333
Mrs. Madrigal, is Amanda?

192
00:12:09,733 --> 00:12:11,333
Will you shut up?

193
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,733
Fine!
She may have outsmarted me once.

194
00:12:18,133 --> 00:12:20,667
But it will never happen again.

195
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:25,433
She may be powerful now
because she has money.

196
00:12:25,567 --> 00:12:31,233
But I still have the most
powerful weapon against her.

197
00:12:32,933 --> 00:12:34,600
Her daughter.

198
00:12:34,733 --> 00:12:36,167
You really are something.

199
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:37,467
I know!

200
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,033
So you.

201
00:12:39,167 --> 00:12:41,433
You should stop pestering me.

202
00:12:41,567 --> 00:12:45,067
Find out who is sabotaging us.

203
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:49,267
I want to find out if he has
a connection with Amanda.

204
00:12:49,433 --> 00:12:51,000
Yes, Rina. Actually I already
have a lead

205
00:12:51,133 --> 00:12:54,200
on where the fake money
came from.

206
00:12:54,333 --> 00:12:55,200
He will confess in no time.

207
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:56,400
Good.

208
00:12:59,267 --> 00:13:05,367
It's our turn to take revenge.

209
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:10,133
Eden was just hurt too.

210
00:13:10,267 --> 00:13:11,600
That's why she said that.

211
00:13:13,533 --> 00:13:16,067
Your daughter loves
you so much, Amanda.

212
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:22,267
And she doesn't want
you to hate each other.

213
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:26,100
Or maybe she really
doesn't need me anymore.

214
00:13:26,233 --> 00:13:29,933
Because she already
has her Mommy Rina.

215
00:13:33,833 --> 00:13:35,800
So...

216
00:13:35,933 --> 00:13:37,867
I'll talk to her.

217
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:38,900
You don't have to.

218
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:42,633
Rina has already
poisoned her mind.

219
00:13:42,767 --> 00:13:45,233
That's why she's
so upset with me.

220
00:13:47,167 --> 00:13:50,367
So, are you just going
to give up on Eden?

221
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:51,633
No.

222
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:56,600
I will never give
up on my daughter.

223
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:58,067
That's the reason
I came back...

224
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,233
for Yenyen.

225
00:14:01,167 --> 00:14:04,700
We already have plans
on how to get her back.

226
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:07,067
Plans?

227
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:13,000
You don't need to
know every detail.

228
00:14:13,133 --> 00:14:17,500
But rest assured,
that Eden will be with you

229
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:19,167
as soon as possible.

230
00:14:39,433 --> 00:14:41,833
I heard you've met your mom.

231
00:14:41,967 --> 00:14:45,900
Is it true that you told
her to forget about you?

232
00:14:49,933 --> 00:14:51,400
Are you with her?

233
00:14:51,533 --> 00:14:52,800
Yes, I'm here.

234
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:54,400
You should be here too.

235
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:56,433
I don't need
to be there, Auntie.

236
00:14:56,567 --> 00:15:00,133
I don't want to mess
with her new life.

237
00:15:00,267 --> 00:15:01,667
What are you saying?

238
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,100
What mess are you
talking about?

239
00:15:03,233 --> 00:15:04,667
You are her daughter.

240
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,633
She only sees me as a burden.

241
00:15:07,767 --> 00:15:11,200
That's what Mommy Rina told me.

242
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:13,567
Mom didn't deny it.

243
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:14,967
So I get it.

244
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:18,433
Please, don't force me, Auntie.

245
00:15:18,567 --> 00:15:20,533
I'm okay being here.

246
00:15:20,667 --> 00:15:25,033
And they treat me as family.

247
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,967
Yenyen...

248
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:34,933
Auntie?

249
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:38,300
Hello, Auntie?

250
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,133
Auntie?

251
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:51,400
Didn't I tell you
not to talk to her?

252
00:15:53,133 --> 00:15:57,067
I'm just trying to convince her
to be with us.

253
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:02,567
It's not that easy.

254
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:07,300
I saw how Rina manipulates Eden.

255
00:16:09,767 --> 00:16:10,800
Can you please avoid her?

256
00:16:10,933 --> 00:16:16,600
You might tell her something
about our life here...

257
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:18,367
about our plans.

258
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:24,033
I don't know anything
about your plans.

259
00:16:24,167 --> 00:16:27,400
And are you really going
to fight with Rina again?

260
00:16:27,533 --> 00:16:29,700
Are you going to take
revenge once again?

261
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:31,467
Why not?

262
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,367
I've changed.

263
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:36,267
I'm no longer the poor
ex-convicted

264
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,467
they used to oppress.

265
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,867
Someone strong has
got my back now.

266
00:16:44,033 --> 00:16:45,900
They can't bring me down.

267
00:16:48,867 --> 00:16:51,567
Looks like your husband
has a bad influence on you.

268
00:16:53,167 --> 00:16:58,833
Lucho saved me after Rina
tortured and threw me

269
00:16:58,967 --> 00:17:00,333
in the garbage.

270
00:17:00,467 --> 00:17:03,033
And after pushing
me to kill myself.

271
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:09,867
I almost got crazy.

272
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,367
But Lucho took care of me.

273
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,800
And he still supports
me up until now.

274
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:22,200
I didn't know that
you'd been through hell.

275
00:17:23,967 --> 00:17:26,833
So I should take
revenge on Rina.

276
00:17:26,967 --> 00:17:28,967
I will expose that woman.

277
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:32,967
So that Eden will
see her mistake.

278
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:37,933
I hope it's only Rina who will
get hurt by your plans.

279
00:17:38,067 --> 00:17:41,300
What if Eden got involved?

280
00:17:42,767 --> 00:17:46,900
She might stay away
instead of going back to us.

281
00:17:58,533 --> 00:18:00,033
Just a bit more.

282
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:01,500
I might trip.

283
00:18:01,633 --> 00:18:02,700
No.

284
00:18:04,367 --> 00:18:05,433
Just close your eyes.

285
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:06,600
What have you got?

286
00:18:06,733 --> 00:18:09,633
- What's your gimmick this time?
- You'll see.

287
00:18:09,767 --> 00:18:10,633
You'll see.

288
00:18:10,767 --> 00:18:12,767
- I'm nervous.
- We're almost there.

289
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:14,100
One more stop.

290
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:19,800
Surprise!

291
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:31,233
I want to make it up to you,
so I asked Emma for help.

292
00:18:31,367 --> 00:18:34,967
We recreated what
you did for me.

293
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:36,467
Did you like it?

294
00:18:38,767 --> 00:18:41,900
Of course.
But why do you look sad?

295
00:18:45,033 --> 00:18:46,200
Sorry.

296
00:18:47,867 --> 00:18:51,100
I really have plans
for our quality time, Red.

297
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:56,233
But Aunt Dindi called.

298
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:58,267
She's with my mom already.

299
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,333
I didn't want
to get affected, but...

300
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:04,567
No, I understand.

301
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,767
But I don't want
you to get sad.

302
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,500
Where's your killer smile?

303
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:12,833
I miss it.

304
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:18,167
There!
Silly.

305
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:22,800
That's the reason
I fell for you.

306
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:33,967
I sometimes miss the island.

307
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:36,867
It's so peaceful there.

308
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:40,467
We don't worry about
our problems here.

309
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:43,567
It's like we're not
in the real world.

310
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:46,667
I want to forget
all our problems.

311
00:19:48,133 --> 00:19:49,833
Yen...

312
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,733
we don't need to be on the
island to forget our problems.

313
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:58,467
I'm here.

314
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:00,933
I'll help you forget.

315
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:04,433
Really?

316
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:07,400
I miss you so much.

317
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:09,300
I missed you too.

318
00:20:11,867 --> 00:20:13,100
Wow!

319
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:15,500
Why you're so sweet.

320
00:20:16,467 --> 00:20:19,633
What are you doing
here again, Sabina?

321
00:20:20,167 --> 00:20:21,900
What are you doing
here again, Sabina?

322
00:20:22,533 --> 00:20:24,400
Come on, Yenyen.

323
00:20:24,533 --> 00:20:26,567
Can't we be friends?

324
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:29,200
I'm here to invite you
to my birthday party.

325
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:31,867
Are you inviting me too?

326
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,700
Of course!

327
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:35,033
Red and I are friends.

328
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,233
So maybe we can
be friends too.

329
00:20:38,367 --> 00:20:40,233
Right, Red?

330
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:43,733
Sab, I don't think
Yenyen is ready.

331
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,467
Why?

332
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:50,933
Don't tell me you're
still insecure with me?

333
00:20:51,067 --> 00:20:54,533
- Sab...
- Yenyen, you already have Red.

334
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:57,300
No? Okay, fine.

335
00:20:57,433 --> 00:20:58,733
I'm sorry.

336
00:20:58,867 --> 00:21:03,300
Look, I'm just saying
congratulations.

337
00:21:03,433 --> 00:21:05,167
Maybe you and Red are
meant for each other.

338
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:10,233
So maybe we can put
the past behind us?

339
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:13,033
Let's be friends, Yenyen.

340
00:21:18,633 --> 00:21:19,667
Really?

341
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,867
Great! So come to my party.

342
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:26,033
So you'll have an
excuse to look good...

343
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:27,933
and dress up a little.

344
00:21:28,067 --> 00:21:29,133
You know?

345
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:30,033
Once...

346
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:31,633
in a while.

347
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:39,600
I won't let them abuse me.

348
00:21:39,733 --> 00:21:44,867
And I won't let them be part
of my and Eden's life forever.

349
00:21:45,033 --> 00:21:49,200
So I will show Eden how
evil people they are.

350
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:54,333
Because once Eden gets hurt,
I'm sure she'll come back to me.

351
00:21:54,467 --> 00:21:57,400
If you're not comfortable
going, we can just stay here.

352
00:21:57,533 --> 00:22:00,600
But is it okay
if I give her a gift?

353
00:22:04,133 --> 00:22:06,200
That's what you get.

354
00:22:06,333 --> 00:22:09,267
You messed
with the wrong people.

355
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:12,100
Who bought that fake
money to pay me?

356
00:22:12,233 --> 00:22:13,667
Is that Amanda Madrigal?

357
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:14,433
Answer me!

358
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:17,767
Can we bring Rina down sooner?

359
00:22:17,933 --> 00:22:20,133
Before more people get involved.

360
00:22:20,267 --> 00:22:23,967
She might hurt Eden too, and do
the exact revenge against me.

361
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:26,233
I want to take my daughter
back from that woman.

362
00:22:26,367 --> 00:22:27,167
Don't worry.

363
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:29,000
We'll need to adjust the plan.
